      "content": "Right, it's definitely a balance. But I keep hearing that the 'benefit to the economy' part is basically just a way to justify these hikes even when they're clearly hurting the actual shops on Main Street. Is there any real, concrete evidence that this policy actually helps people in small towns, or is it mostly just a way to push an agenda that works better in big cities?",
